30:47.201 --> 30:52.281
Have you ever heard of an Italian being
a tourist in Rome in the past 20 years ?

30:53.001 --> 30:55.241
No, it's our turn then.

30:55.761 --> 30:57.401
In a car ? No.

30:57.681 --> 30:59.601
On foot. Almost.

31:01.481 --> 31:03.241
- Almost.
- Almost.

31:05.801 --> 31:07.521
Hi, Daniele.
Thanks a million.

31:07.681 --> 31:08.801
Voilà !

31:10.601 --> 31:13.921
Cool, huh ?
It doesn't even have brakes.

31:14.081 --> 31:15.401
Shit!

31:15.961 --> 31:17.641
- Where's he going ?
- Out of the way !

31:23.841 --> 31:25.001
Shitheads.

31:25.281 --> 31:27.201
You're total shitheads.

31:28.281 --> 31:29.481
What's so fucking funny ?

31:48.961 --> 31:50.321
Thanks, Giulio, really.

31:50.601 --> 31:52.721
- No problem. Behave.
- Don't worry.

31:52.881 --> 31:55.001
Guys, we've got half an hour,
come on.

31:57.121 --> 31:58.161
Thanks.

32:02.121 --> 32:05.241
- What did you tell him ?
- That you had two months to live.

32:05.881 --> 32:07.241
You bastard !

32:07.401 --> 32:09.281
You wanted to come here, right ?

34:12.761 --> 34:15.201
I could do with a new back !

34:17.801 --> 34:19.880
Cool, huh ?

34:20.321 --> 34:22.400
A breath-taking view.

34:29.400 --> 34:30.641
No?

34:32.561 --> 34:34.601
Is he worse than usual ?

34:37.440 --> 34:39.360
So, what shall we do ?

34:41.400 --> 34:43.001
Good question.

34:45.481 --> 34:47.521
Good morning, partners in crime !

34:48.440 --> 34:51.761
I'm fine with "partner",
not sure about the "crime" though.

34:52.601 --> 34:54.081
Are we ready ?

34:54.241 --> 34:55.440
Shall we go ?

34:56.281 --> 34:58.721
Riko, are you sure ?

34:58.881 --> 35:00.361
Yes, yes...

35:00.761 --> 35:02.921
Going or not makes no difference.

35:04.641 --> 35:07.401
I'm not talking to you,
but to my co-worker.

35:07.881 --> 35:10.241
What are we going to do
down there, Riko ?

35:11.521 --> 35:13.641
Something needs to be done.

35:14.841 --> 35:17.161
Something needs to be done.

35:31.761 --> 35:34.561
Hands off! Hands off!

35:36.441 --> 35:38.681
Hands off! Hands off!

35:38.841 --> 35:41.081
<i>Hands off Article 18 !</i>

35:41.241 --> 35:43.281
Hands off! Hands off!

35:43.441 --> 35:45.161
<i>Hands off Article 18 !</i>

35:45.641 --> 35:47.841
Hands off! Hands off!

35:48.001 --> 35:50.241
<i>Hands off Article 18 !</i>

35:50.401 --> 35:51.401
Hands off!

35:51.961 --> 35:55.401
<i>This is a planned demonstration,
we have the right to protest.</i>

35:55.601 --> 35:58.321
<i>Make way !
We need to join the main protest.</i>

35:58.681 --> 36:01.641
Police, go away !
Police, go away !

36:01.801 --> 36:04.121
- Let us through <i>!</i>
- Police, go away !

36:04.561 --> 36:06.081
Police, go away !

36:06.281 --> 36:08.401
<i>Stop, be quiet !
Stop !</i>

36:08.601 --> 36:09.961
<i>Let us through !</i>

36:10.121 --> 36:13.201
<i>Make way !
We need to join the main protest.</i>

36:13.681 --> 36:15.761
<i>We're allowed to protest !</i>

36:16.521 --> 36:17.601
What the fuck are you doing ?

36:17.761 --> 36:19.401
- They'll attack us !
- They sure will now!

36:19.561 --> 36:22.281
Stand over there and don't move !

36:24.481 --> 36:26.961
<i>You have no right to stop us !</i>

37:04.041 --> 37:06.801
A 20-minute queue for coffee.

37:07.321 --> 37:09.761
I can't believe I'm your nurse now.

37:12.681 --> 37:15.041
Well... cheers, then.

37:21.041 --> 37:23.281
Max Lionheart says hi.

37:23.441 --> 37:25.561
See how shit scared he was ?

37:30.841 --> 37:32.641
Get back to bed.

37:39.481 --> 37:42.921
I don't need to hold your hand,
you're in better shape than me.

37:43.121 --> 37:46.681
I've had my coffee, so I'll scoot off.

37:47.681 --> 37:49.961
- There, perfect timing.
- Hi.

37:50.561 --> 37:52.161
Hi.

38:00.001 --> 38:02.001
I've brought you some clothes.

38:03.041 --> 38:05.881
He's still in one piece, he's all yours.

38:06.521 --> 38:07.721
I'll be off.

38:13.041 --> 38:13.961
Thanks.

38:14.161 --> 38:16.601
A whack on the head
did him good.

38:18.481 --> 38:19.761
Bye.

38:23.001 --> 38:24.321
Shall I put it there ?

38:24.481 --> 38:25.481
Yes.

38:27.681 --> 38:29.041
Well...

38:29.201 --> 38:31.641
I spoke to the doctor...

38:31.801 --> 38:34.401
You were lucky, it's nothing serious.

38:35.521 --> 38:38.441
They just want to keep you here
to be safe.

38:42.361 --> 38:43.681
Oh, yes... Pietro.

38:43.841 --> 38:46.681
He knows you're fine,
but wants to see you. Okay ?

38:46.841 --> 38:48.041
Yes.

38:51.281 --> 38:52.681
Here, wait...

38:53.441 --> 38:55.561
<i>- Hi.</i>
- Hi.

38:55.721 --> 38:57.561
- Here he is.
<i>- Well?</i>

38:57.761 --> 39:01.001
<i>It was your first protest
and you end up in hospital?</i>

39:01.161 --> 39:04.721
It wasn't the first,
you just hadn't been born yet.

39:04.881 --> 39:06.801
<i>You wanna be a rockstar, huh ?</i>

39:06.961 --> 39:10.881
<i>The video of you getting truncheoned
has had a billion views.</i>

39:11.041 --> 39:14.081
<i>By the way, some newspapers
want to interview you.</i>

39:14.641 --> 39:16.361
<i>What shall I tell them ?</i>

39:16.521 --> 39:18.521
<i>Have a think then let me know.</i>

39:18.961 --> 39:21.041
<i>Well, you guys look happy.</i>

39:21.921 --> 39:24.481
<i>Spend a few days in Rome
and have a riot.</i>

39:25.081 --> 39:27.521
<i>Oh God, "have a riot"...
What a horrible thought !</i>

39:28.041 --> 39:29.641
<i>- Bye.
- Bye.</i>

39:38.881 --> 39:40.921
If there's nothing you need, I'll go.

39:41.841 --> 39:44.681
After all... you're in good hands.

39:45.201 --> 39:47.881
The doctor... she's a good-looking lady.

39:50.521 --> 39:52.481
Well, see you tomorrow.

39:52.641 --> 39:54.601
You don't need to come.

39:54.761 --> 39:58.481
I'm staying in a hotel nearby,
so I can be here for a few days.

39:59.841 --> 40:02.441
Maybe we'll go back together.

40:02.641 --> 40:04.761
I mean... we'll go home together.

40:06.161 --> 40:08.321
Well, bye.

40:41.361 --> 40:42.881
That was Angela.

40:43.041 --> 40:47.121
They wanted to come to Rome to visit you,
but I told her we're leaving.

40:47.281 --> 40:50.961
Here you are !
Some journalists want to see you.

40:51.361 --> 40:55.401
They know you're getting discharged so...
shall I send them up ?

40:55.801 --> 40:59.321
I suggest you see them today,
or tomorrow it'll be worse.

41:04.561 --> 41:08.161
The images you've just seen
have gone viral.

41:08.321 --> 41:11.841
During Tuesday's clashes a protester
was hit by a policeman

41:12.001 --> 41:14.601
with a truncheon, causing a gash
on his forehead.

41:14.761 --> 41:18.481
We're at the hospital where this protester
is being treated.

41:18.641 --> 41:22.521
Luckily, he's out of danger
and he's here with us: Riccardo Tirelli.

41:23.281 --> 41:25.561
So, Riccardo, you...

41:25.761 --> 41:28.561
and many others like you,
came to Rome

41:28.721 --> 41:31.681
to exercise your right
to stand up for your rights.

41:32.681 --> 41:35.201
It was a peaceful protest

41:35.361 --> 41:38.641
and then, suddenly, you were attacked.

41:39.521 --> 41:42.921
Actually, I didn't even make it
as far as the protest.

41:43.081 --> 41:45.241
- And we weren't attacked.
- So...

41:45.721 --> 41:48.161
Tell us what happened.

41:48.601 --> 41:50.041
Well...

41:50.201 --> 41:53.241
Me and two friends of mine
got caught up in a group

41:53.401 --> 41:56.241
that was trying to join the protest.

41:56.401 --> 41:59.561
They were already hyped up,
with megaphones, chanting...

41:59.721 --> 42:02.001
A sort of spontaneous fringe gathering.

42:02.161 --> 42:03.721
More or less...

42:03.881 --> 42:08.481
The street was being blocked
by a group of policemen.

42:09.161 --> 42:13.041
- Insults started flying...
- And that's when you were attacked.

42:14.121 --> 42:16.401
We were the ones who attacked.

42:18.801 --> 42:20.961
It's the game of roles.

42:22.161 --> 42:24.521
Every day you get mad
and you suck it up.

42:25.121 --> 42:28.641
You get mad and you suck it up.
You resist and resist, until one day...

42:28.801 --> 42:31.961
you either blow your top
or take it out on someone.

42:32.601 --> 42:35.001
None of us wanted to take it out
on the police.

42:35.841 --> 42:38.121
- But they were sent there.
- And then ?

42:39.361 --> 42:43.441
And then you go back to making
salami for 1,200 euros a month,

42:43.601 --> 42:45.681
after 30 years in the same job,

42:45.841 --> 42:48.241
to seeing your retirement age
get further away,

42:48.921 --> 42:52.921
to having your house robbed of
the few things you own every 5 years,

42:53.681 --> 42:55.801
to praying that you or your family
don't get sick

42:56.001 --> 42:58.921
'cause you'll wait 8 months
for a scan.

42:59.201 --> 43:02.041
In a few months,
my son's starting a Drama degree.

43:04.761 --> 43:07.521
He's the first in the family
to go to uni.

43:08.321 --> 43:11.881
For some reason, he's fond
of the area where he grew up.

43:13.241 --> 43:15.561
What's the likelihood of him staying there

43:15.721 --> 43:20.081
or joining the hundred thousand
people who emigrate every year ?

43:21.641 --> 43:24.361
The images are very gory,

43:24.521 --> 43:27.121
they show that you lost a lot of blood

43:27.361 --> 43:29.641
and that you fainted after you were hit.

43:29.801 --> 43:31.881
But what I want to ask you is:

43:32.041 --> 43:36.881
do you remember what you were thinking
at that moment when...

43:38.081 --> 43:40.321
you lost consciousness ?

43:41.041 --> 43:43.041
I was thinking that...

43:44.121 --> 43:45.841
I didn't want to think about anything.

43:46.041 --> 43:50.121
Maybe this last phrase sums up
all the frustration

43:50.321 --> 43:52.201
felt by a category that feels invisible.

43:52.401 --> 43:55.521
Hold on...
I'm not a category, okay ?

43:55.681 --> 43:58.041
I'm just speaking for myself.
Hey, I'm up here.

43:58.201 --> 44:00.281
I only speak for myself.

44:00.481 --> 44:02.601
Okay.

44:02.801 --> 44:04.841
We're done, I think that'll do.

44:08.481 --> 44:09.521
Hi.

44:10.321 --> 44:11.681
Hi, mum.

44:13.201 --> 44:15.321
Come on, dinner's ready.

44:16.441 --> 44:18.361
You mean that you cooked ?

44:18.521 --> 44:21.161
Indian take-away. Martina brought it.

44:22.081 --> 44:23.441
Martina ?

44:39.041 --> 44:40.721
Come on, let's go !

44:45.161 --> 44:48.081
<i>Now, to end the report
on Tuesday's protest,</i>

44:48.241 --> 44:50.721
<i>let's hear from someone
who was wounded in the clashes.</i>

44:51.321 --> 44:56.401
<i>The images are very gory,
they show that you lost a lot of blood.</i>

44:57.281 --> 45:00.601
<i>Do you remember what you were thinking</i>

45:00.801 --> 45:02.921
<i>at that moment when
you lost consciousness ?</i>

45:04.481 --> 45:06.001
<i>I was thinking that...</i>

45:07.761 --> 45:09.161
<i>I didn't want to think about anything.</i>

45:09.321 --> 45:11.801
<i>Now for our report on nutrition.</i>

45:13.401 --> 45:15.761
You'll win an Oscar!

45:17.201 --> 45:19.321
You're a film star!

45:33.481 --> 45:35.161
You showed them, Riko !

45:35.361 --> 45:37.081
More like they showed me.

45:37.241 --> 45:40.561
You wanted to bust that truncheon
with your head.

46:07.281 --> 46:08.881
Riko !

46:09.041 --> 46:10.881
- Do you like Indian food ?
- Yes.

46:11.401 --> 46:14.321
Do you want to try real Indian food ?
Come to lunch on Sunday.

46:14.481 --> 46:16.561
- Bring your wife.
- Great, thanks.

46:16.961 --> 46:19.841
- See you Sunday. You know where I live.
- Bye.

46:24.321 --> 46:27.681
I know, they've split up three
or four times but always make up.

46:27.841 --> 46:30.401
Patrizio in a steady relationship ?
No way !

46:31.121 --> 46:32.841
Let's see, maybe.

46:37.841 --> 46:39.361
Anyway, you look happy.

46:40.001 --> 46:41.081
I am happy.

46:42.441 --> 46:43.761
But?

46:47.001 --> 46:48.801
But you still haven't told him.

46:51.281 --> 46:53.161
Don't tell him, not ever.

46:53.641 --> 46:54.961
Don't tell him.

46:56.761 --> 46:58.801
And stop having all those doubts.

47:00.561 --> 47:03.721
I love our Monday lunches.
Let's do it more often !

47:19.281 --> 47:20.481
Hi.

47:22.881 --> 47:24.921
I was worried.

47:26.321 --> 47:28.121
There's no need.

47:29.801 --> 47:32.401
So, want to tell me about it?

47:32.961 --> 47:35.001
I'm sure you've heard it all.

47:42.961 --> 47:44.921
No, don't.

47:47.761 --> 47:48.841
No!

47:49.121 --> 47:50.281
I mean it, no.

47:51.361 --> 47:52.561
No?

47:55.841 --> 47:57.041
This is no good.

47:57.361 --> 47:58.881
"This is no good ?".

47:59.041 --> 48:00.761
What do you mean ?

48:01.761 --> 48:04.241
You're the first guy
to ever refuse a blow job.

48:05.041 --> 48:07.561
Edda... let's call it off, okay.

48:07.761 --> 48:10.001
Who are you screwing ?

48:10.201 --> 48:12.321
Sogliani ? Tedeschi ?

48:16.721 --> 48:19.761
One of these days
I'll go get my hair cut by your wife !

48:19.921 --> 48:22.841
I'm dying to have a long chat with her!

48:37.561 --> 48:39.441
I'm outside, come out.

48:39.841 --> 48:42.241
No, I'm not coming in.
You come out.

49:04.241 --> 49:05.441
Well?

49:06.601 --> 49:09.401
- Haven't we said "enough" enough ?
- I'll decide when it's enough.

49:09.761 --> 49:11.121
You'll decide ?

49:11.801 --> 49:14.841
- They broke your wrists last year.
- Are you my uncle ?

49:15.881 --> 49:18.481
- I'm watching, not playing.
- Sure !

49:19.041 --> 49:21.881
What about the casino in Venice ?
Every other day.

49:22.361 --> 49:25.241
And the fruit machines in the county ?
Every other day...

49:26.481 --> 49:29.321
Do you expect us to just sit back
and watch you ?

49:29.841 --> 49:33.521
No, mind your own goddamn business.
And you...

49:34.041 --> 49:36.801
You know how it works with junkies.

49:36.961 --> 49:38.961
You have to hit rock bottom.

49:44.161 --> 49:45.801
I'll be all right.

49:46.561 --> 49:47.681
See you on Friday.

49:54.561 --> 49:55.841
Hi, guys.

49:56.601 --> 49:58.081
- How are you ?
- Good.

50:05.761 --> 50:07.041
Come on in.

50:22.761 --> 50:24.521
My father.

51:13.881 --> 51:16.121
I ate like there's no tomorrow !

51:16.281 --> 51:18.041
Sorry, what ?

51:18.201 --> 51:21.081
I've never eaten so much
in all my life.

51:21.241 --> 51:23.721
- You didn't eat a lot.
- Yes, I did !

51:26.281 --> 51:28.361
- How long have you lived here ?
- I was born here.

51:32.201 --> 51:36.321
Why did your parents choose a place
with the world's worst climate ?

51:37.121 --> 51:40.601
My father's brother lived here
and he persuaded him.

51:41.961 --> 51:44.721
I like it here, I always have.

51:46.201 --> 51:48.521
You're a beautiful family.

51:49.241 --> 51:52.281
You remind me of the stories
my father used to tell me.

51:53.601 --> 51:55.961
He lived with five siblings...

51:56.161 --> 51:59.001
- His parents, and grandparents...
- Don't you like your family ?

51:59.481 --> 52:01.361
Don't you have kids ?

52:01.521 --> 52:04.481
We have a son,
who's almost as old as you.

52:05.521 --> 52:07.761
We wanted to have many more.

52:09.201 --> 52:11.721
But I wasn't able to have any more...

52:13.601 --> 52:15.441
after Luca.

52:16.641 --> 52:19.641
I lost him when I was six months pregnant.

52:20.601 --> 52:23.041
A few more days and he'd have made it.

52:25.761 --> 52:29.081
In these cases the doctors suggest
you see the baby,

52:29.241 --> 52:31.361
otherwise goodness knows
what you'll imagine...

52:32.241 --> 52:35.161
So we held him for a few minutes.

52:41.041 --> 52:42.961
He was perfect.

52:45.801 --> 52:47.041
He had...

52:47.201 --> 52:48.881
Riko's hands !

52:52.361 --> 52:53.601
He was perfect.

52:59.281 --> 53:02.561
I've always wondered
if he managed to take...

53:02.721 --> 53:04.881
at least one breath of our air.

53:06.601 --> 53:07.961
I'm sorry.

53:08.161 --> 53:10.601
It was a long time ago.

53:13.961 --> 53:16.161
Have you been married long ?

53:17.521 --> 53:18.681
Very long.

53:21.761 --> 53:23.521
Maybe too long.

53:26.601 --> 53:29.121
Pavak always says that he's a good man.

53:29.881 --> 53:32.161
- Really ?
- He always says:

53:32.761 --> 53:33.801
"Honest".

53:36.201 --> 53:37.641
Honest...

53:41.001 --> 53:43.401
That's not a family.

53:43.561 --> 53:45.801
- It's an asylum.
- What commotion.

53:48.801 --> 53:51.001
Wonderful commotion.

53:57.841 --> 53:59.281
I need to tell you something.

55:06.521 --> 55:08.601
However much you think I'm a shit,

55:08.761 --> 55:10.761
just know that I feel even worse.

55:11.721 --> 55:15.441
But I've not come to say sorry,
I know that's not enough.

55:15.601 --> 55:18.281
I came to tell you that it was my fault.

55:18.761 --> 55:20.881
And partly her fault too...

55:22.201 --> 55:23.721
But also yours !

55:23.881 --> 55:26.761
Because you don't realise
who you're living with.

55:26.921 --> 55:29.961
And how lucky you are !
It wasn't done to spite you !

55:31.401 --> 55:32.961
It wasn't.

56:03.001 --> 56:05.561
I don't have time to eat now,
sit down.

56:07.081 --> 56:08.521
Please.

56:11.321 --> 56:13.281
Please, sit down.

56:24.921 --> 56:28.641
I know what happens now,
you simply don't say a word.

56:29.401 --> 56:32.561
And I don't know what you're thinking,
but I imagine the worst.

56:34.081 --> 56:36.481
But you're fine with that,
so you don't have to ask.

56:36.641 --> 56:38.801
Because you never ask, not ever.

56:40.401 --> 56:43.481
You never ask how my day's been,

56:43.641 --> 56:47.001
whether I want to do something different,
or what I'm thinking,

56:47.201 --> 56:49.241
or what I'm feeling...

56:52.361 --> 56:54.601
So I end up doing a monologue.

56:55.321 --> 56:57.081
This time too.

57:04.761 --> 57:06.921
It happened only once.

57:08.441 --> 57:10.441
Just once.

57:12.081 --> 57:14.441
It shouldn't have happened, I know.

57:16.521 --> 57:20.081
But it happened only... once.

57:24.001 --> 57:25.961
Is that enough for you ?

57:27.761 --> 57:29.921
That's enough, yes.

57:32.441 --> 57:35.681
Because I've never felt so guilty
in all my life.

57:38.441 --> 57:40.601
And I've never been so disgusted
with myself.

57:43.121 --> 57:46.001
Because you need to know,
that in this case too,

57:47.281 --> 57:50.321
like in every other moment
during all these years together,

57:50.481 --> 57:52.361
I've never...

57:52.521 --> 57:54.281
and I mean never,

57:55.721 --> 57:58.881
I've never budged an inch,
not even for one second.

57:59.041 --> 58:00.801
I have always been here.

58:03.041 --> 58:06.001
Even when I knew for a fact
that you were screwing around.

58:19.001 --> 58:21.241
I think about Luca every day.

58:22.281 --> 58:24.281
Still now.

58:26.841 --> 58:29.241
Sometimes I have the feeling...

58:31.241 --> 58:33.401
the physical feeling, that he's here.

58:35.921 --> 58:38.161
And still now, every day,

58:38.921 --> 58:41.881
I think about how you were there for me
when we lost him.

58:44.241 --> 58:46.201
But it's always been that way.

58:46.361 --> 58:49.721
You and I have always stuck together
through everything,

58:49.881 --> 58:51.841
everything.

58:52.121 --> 58:53.601
And we're still here.

58:57.801 --> 59:00.521
