<i>As I've got plenty of time to think,
I was wondering:</i>

01:31:09.681 --> 01:31:14.441
<i>"How come we're still us ?</i>

01:31:16.561 --> 01:31:20.361
<i>What's that particle made of
that survives once our cells die ?"</i>

01:31:23.241 --> 01:31:25.081
<i>I'm made of my family,</i>

01:31:26.481 --> 01:31:29.801
<i>I'm made of you,
of Max, of all the others.</i>

01:31:30.521 --> 01:31:33.801
<i>We're made of our small city,
of its walls,</i>

01:31:34.321 --> 01:31:37.521
<i>of the stories we've been told about it
and of others like us.</i>

01:31:38.241 --> 01:31:40.001
<i>We're made of that air.</i>

01:31:41.081 --> 01:31:43.241
<i>I know you'll laugh
when I tell you that I've realized</i>

01:31:43.401 --> 01:31:45.481
<i>what being homesick means.</i>

01:31:46.281 --> 01:31:47.601
<i>But it's true.</i>

01:31:47.761 --> 01:31:51.041
<i>It's so strong I sometimes think
that you can't confine air.</i>

01:31:52.201 --> 01:31:55.561
<i>Then it seems like I can see,
from here, from far away,</i>

01:31:55.921 --> 01:31:57.681
<i>that perhaps in some way,</i>

01:31:58.041 --> 01:32:02.041
<i>somehow,
we're also made of Trieste,</i>

01:32:02.201 --> 01:32:03.801
<i>Milan, Cagliari,</i>

01:32:04.441 --> 01:32:05.961
<i>Lecce, Venice,</i>

01:32:06.601 --> 01:32:08.161
<i>Pescara, Palermo.</i>

01:32:09.361 --> 01:32:12.121
<i>Perhaps we're made of beauty
and putridness.</i>

01:32:12.441 --> 01:32:14.641
<i>Of lies, of fear.</i>

01:32:14.961 --> 01:32:16.761
<i>Of chaos and wonders.</i>

01:32:18.041 --> 01:32:20.321
<i>And we're also made of last ditch efforts.</i>

01:32:20.481 --> 01:32:22.481
<i>A series of last ditch efforts.</i>

01:32:23.761 --> 01:32:26.121
<i>We're made of contempt...</i>

01:32:27.281 --> 01:32:28.441
<i>and yes...</i>

01:32:28.841 --> 01:32:30.001
of love.

01:32:31.841 --> 01:32:33.801
<i>Do you think I've become sentimental ?</i>

01:32:35.681 --> 01:32:36.961
<i>Yes...</i>

01:32:38.121 --> 01:32:40.401
<i>I'm waiting to see how things work out.</i>

01:32:41.001 --> 01:32:44.841
<i>But at least I know they will work out,
I'm sure of that.</i>

01:32:46.281 --> 01:32:49.201
<i>Wherever you are,
take care of yourself.</i>

01:32:50.161 --> 01:32:53.361
<i>And wherever you are,
I'm sending you a big hug.</i>

01:32:54.401 --> 01:32:58.761
<i>P.S. The other day Pietro sent me
an email with a quote by Cesare Pavese.</i>

01:32:58.921 --> 01:33:00.161
<i>This is what it said:</i>

01:33:00.441 --> 01:33:03.081
<i>"You need a village,</i>

01:33:03.361 --> 01:33:05.841
<i>if only for the pleasure of leaving it.</i>

01:33:06.561 --> 01:33:08.961
<i>Your own village means that
you are not alone.</i>

01:33:09.201 --> 01:33:13.721
<i>That you know that in the people
and the plants and the soil,</i>

01:33:13.961 --> 01:33:15.801
<i>there is something of you,</i>

01:33:15.961 --> 01:33:18.161
<i>that even when you are not there,</i>

01:33:18.321 --> 01:33:20.201
<i>it waits to welcome you back."</i>

